1(b). Increase CPU and RAM by Changing Instance Type
Open EC2 Dashboard
Select the EC2 instance
Click:
Instance State → Stop Instance
After stopping, click:
Actions → Instance Settings → Change Instance Type
Select a higher instance type
Click Apply
Start the instance:
Instance State → Start Instance
2. Permanently Mount an EBS Volume
Step 1: Create Volume
Open EC2 Dashboard
Go to Volumes
Click Create Volume
Choose:
gp3
20 GB
Same AZ as EC2
Click Create Volume
Step 2: Attach Volume
Select volume
Click:
Actions → Attach Volume
Select EC2 instance
Device name:
/dev/xvdf
Click Attach
Step 3: Connect to EC2
ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@public-ip
Step 4: Verify Disk
lsblk
Step 5: Create Partition
sudo fdisk /dev/nvme1n1

Inside fdisk:

n
p
Enter
Enter
Enter
w

Reload partition table:

sudo partprobe
Step 6: Verify Partition
lsblk
Step 7: Format Partition
sudo mkfs.xfs /dev/nvme1n1p1
Step 8: Create Mount Directory
sudo mkdir /mnt/archana
Step 9: Mount Volume
sudo mount /dev/nvme1n1p1 /mnt/archana

Verify:

df -h
Step 10: Permanent Mount

Get UUID:

sudo blkid /dev/nvme1n1p1

Edit fstab:

sudo nano /etc/fstab

Add:

UUID=your-uuid /mnt/archana xfs defaults,nofail 0 0

Test:

sudo mount -a

Create file:

cd /mnt/archana
touch f1
Step 11: Verify Persistence

Reboot:

sudo reboot

Reconnect and verify:

df -h
Step 12: Detach and Reattach

Detach:

Volumes → Actions → Detach Volume

Attach to another EC2 instance.

Mount:

sudo mkdir /mnt/archana
sudo mount /dev/nvme1n1p1 /mnt/archana
3. Snapshot and Cross-Region Volume Creation
Step 1: Create Snapshot
Open EC2 Dashboard
Go to Volumes
Select EBS volume
Click:
Actions → Create Snapshot
Enter name and description
Click Create Snapshot
Step 2: Copy Snapshot to Another Region
Go to Snapshots
Select snapshot
Click:
Actions → Copy Snapshot
Select destination region
Click Copy Snapshot
Step 3: Monitor Snapshot

Wait until status changes:

pending → completed
Step 4: Switch Region

Use region selector in AWS Console.

Step 5: Create Volume from Snapshot
Open Snapshots
Select copied snapshot
Click:
Actions → Create Volume
Configure size/type/AZ
Click Create Volume
Step 6: Attach Volume
Go to Volumes
Select new volume
Click:
Actions → Attach Volume
Select EC2 instance
Click Attach
